{{Infobox writer | name = Armen Weitzman | image = | imagesize = | alt = | caption = | pseudonym = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1983|12|19|mf=yes}}<ref>{{cite tweet|user=katemicucci|author=Kate Micucci|number=413795521263063040|date=19 December 2013|title=Happy Birthday armenweitzman You look very dapper today! 🎂}}</ref><ref>http://birth-records.mooseroots.com/d/b/Armen-Weitzman</ref> | birth_place = [[Los Angeles, California]], U.S. | occupation = Actor and comedian<ref>{{cite web|url=http://losangeles.ucbtheatre.com/talent/view/10598 |title=UCB Theatre • Armen Weitzman |publisher=Losangeles.ucbtheatre.com |date= |accessdate=2013-08-12}}</ref> | nationality = American | citizenship = | education = [[Emerson College]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.communiversity.com/schools/emerson_college/videos.html?school_id=1104&video_id=731691 |title=Videos : Kippins |publisher=Communiversity |date= |accessdate=2013-08-12}}</ref> | alma_mater = | period = | genre = | notableworks = | spouse = | partner = | children = | relatives = [[Howard Weitzman]] (father), [[Max Winkler (director)|Max Winkler]] (step-brother) | awards = | signature = | website = {{URL|http://www.armenweitzman.com/}} | portaldisp = }}
'''Armen Weitzman''' (born December 19, 1983) is an American actor and comedian best known for playing Garfield in the [[Comedy Central]] series ''[[Another Period]]''.
==Life and career== Weitzman was born and raised in [[Los Angeles, California]]. He is a regular performer at the [[Upright Citizens Brigade Theater]] in Los Angeles. He has appeared in television and film projects such as ''[[Burning Love (web series)|Burning Love]], [[The Sarah Silverman Program]], [[Childrens Hospital (TV Series)|Childrens Hospital]], [[Role Models]], [[School for Scoundrels (2006 film)|School for Scoundrels]], [[Love (TV series)|Love]],'' and ''[[Ocean's Thirteen]]'' among other film and television programs. He was also on the short-lived MTV show, ''[[Zach Stone Is Gonna Be Famous]]'', as the title character's best friend.<ref>{{cite web|last=Masters |first=Megan |url=http://tvline.com/2013/03/13/the-show-with-vinny-season-1-mtv-premiere-date/ |title=The Show With Vinny Season 1 — MTV Announces Premiere Date |publisher=TVLine |date=2013-03-13 |accessdate=2013-08-12}}</ref> He currently co-stars as the servant Garfield in the Comedy Central show ''[[Another Period]]'', as Jeff in [[Silicon Valley (TV series)]]<ref>https://www.imdb.com/title/tt2575988/fullcredits</ref> & Netflix's [[Love (TV series)]].<ref>https://www.imdb.com/title/tt4061080/fullcredits?ref_=tt_cl_sm#cast</ref> Weitzman was awarded the Heart of a Chompian Award on the March 30, 2017 episode of Feral Audio's Doughboys podcast.
