'''Ma Fushou''' ({{zh|s=马福寿|t=馬福壽|p=Mǎ Fúshòu}}, [[Xiao'erjing]]: {{lang|zh-Arab|ﻣَﺎ  ﻓُﻮْ ﺷِﻮْ}}), a [[Hui people|Hui]], was the son of General [[Ma Qianling]], and the brother of [[Ma Fucai]], [[Ma Fulu]], and [[Ma Fuxiang]]. He joined the martial arts hall and attended military school after three years of training in 1892.<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=90CN0vtxdY0C&pg=PA168&dq=ma+fulu&hl=en&ei=MywhTNS9LoWBlAfA_JRa&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=1&ved=0CCcQ6AEwAA#v=snippet&q=Ma%20Fushou%20military%20school&f=false|title=Familiar strangers: a history of Muslims in Northwest China|author=Jonathan Neaman Lipman|year=2004|publisher=University of Washington Press|location=Seattle|isbn=0-295-97644-6|page=168|accessdate=2010-06-28}}</ref>

In 1917, Ma Fushou, chief of staff of the Brillitant Military Army and defeated Bandits at Zuuqa temple. Ma Fuxiang dispatched Fushou with an army to attack Kao's army at zuuqa temple, and destroyed all the bandits.<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=0I7ML6rrzN0C&pg=PA54&lpg=PA54&dq=ma+fu-hsiang&source=bl&ots=uur78UuNGE&sig=C6cLFNIE8tt5ao-v_lRT_FYWjgg&hl=en&ei=m3gzTOrKKMKblgeO9MTECw&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=7&ved=0CCsQ6AEwBg#v=snippet&q=chief%20ma%20fu-shou%20of%20staff&f=false|title=Etudes Mongoles et Sibériennes|author=Centre d'études mongoles et sibériennes|year=|publisher=SEMS|location=|page=53|isbn=|accessdate=2010-06-28}}</ref>

Ma Fushou was over 90 years old when died in 1956 in Linxia.<ref>[http://www.360doc.com/content/11/0917/16/112480_149020067.shtml 民国少数民族将军(组图)2 - 360Doc个人图书馆]</ref>

[[File:Chiang Kaishek with Muslim General Ma Fushou.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Ma Fushou with [[Chiang Kai-shek]]]]

